==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Moth-eat
<hw>Moth"-eat`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To eat or prey
upon, as a moth eats a garment.</def> <mark>[Rarely used except in the
form <it>moth-eaten</it>, p. p. or a.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Ruin and neglect have so <qex>moth-eaten</qex> her.</q>
<rj><qau>Sir T. Herbert.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Moth-eaten</ent>⟦br⟧
